data.event: The Russian-Germans in 1878, the Poles in 1888 and the Italians in 1890 led by Giovanni Rossi, with the latter formed the first anarchist colony of America, Cecilia Colony.

And, in 1951, came the German Mennonites who founded the Witmarsum Colony and the Witmarsum Joint Agricultural Cooperative Ltd. (Cooperativa Mista Agropecu√°ria Witmarsum Ltda) producer of dairy products, and poultry with Cancela brand.

data.event: Created through State Law No. 238 of November 9, 1897, and installed on the same date, it was separated from Ponta Grossa.
